\begin{align*}
\frac{\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}}{|\mathbf{a}|}=\frac{|\mathbf{a_1}|}{|\mathbf{a}|}, \qquad \frac{\mathbf{c} \cdot \mathbf{b}}{|\mathbf{c}|}=\frac{|\mathbf{c_1}|}{|\mathbf{c}|}. 
\end{align*}
Therefore, $$\mathbf{c}=\alpha\mathbf{b}, \,\,\,\, \text{ where } \,\,\,\, \frac{\alpha}{|\alpha|}=-\frac{\mathbf{a}}{|\mathbf{a}|}$$
The length of $\mathbf{c}$ can be found noting that $$|\mathbf{a}-\alpha \mathbf{b}|^2\,\,\, =\,\,\,|\mathbf{c}|^2$$ which yields 
$$\alpha \,\, =-\sqrt{\frac{|\mathbf{a}|}{\cos \gamma}}$$ Where $\gamma$ is the angle between $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{b}$. </think>
